Signore, professore dottore Eco, what a library you have ! How many of these books have you read?” and the others - a very small minority - who get the point that a private library is not an ego-boosting appendage but a research tool.

About (the academic) me


"Cammino in mezzo agli altri, tutti più o meno uguali
E canto nella testa un poco di Brunori SAS
Faccio parte anch’io di quest’aurea mediocritas.
E vado ricercando medie senza varianza, un pò di stabilità
Male non fa"
Romastino - Translation

I am an Assistant Professor (RtdB) at the Department of Statistics of University of Padua.

Previously, I held the role of Assistant Professor (RtdA) at the Department of Statistics of Università Cattolica del Sacro Cuore - Milan.
Prior to that, I spent two years as a Postdoctoral Scholar at the Department of Statistics of Univerisity of California - Irvine (UCI), working under the supervision of Professor Babak Shahbaba.

I obtained a Ph.D. in Statistics at University of Milan - Bicocca and Università della Svizzera italiana (joint program, awarded with honors) working with Professor Antonietta Mira and Professor Michele Guindani.

I am interested in Bayesian mixtures, Bayesian nonparametrics, model-based clustering, shrinkage priors, and dimensionality reduction.
